                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12750898" author="supun" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2009 08:26:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch that generates a unique name for anonymous endpoints.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12774593" author="indika" created="Sat, 7 Nov 2009 12:48:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Spun thanks for the patch ... But  I feels the  logic for setting the endpoint name should be gone within the endpoint factory.  The code for getting the endpoint name and setting it  seems scatted throughout all endpoint factories. I feels it is better to encapsulate these code into a single place in the abstract endpoint factory and then  to add your code for automatically generating a unique name for anonymous endpoints to that place. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12838667" author="ruwan" created="Fri, 26 Feb 2010 01:59:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Supun, I think Indika is correct, I have introduced a new method into the EndpointFactory and added the logic to guarantee the existance of a name into that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Ruwan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12838668" author="ruwan" created="Fri, 26 Feb 2010 02:00:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed on the trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
